  "text": "HOMER determines all system configurations may be applied, then displayed sequentially according to Net Presents Costs (NPC) or also called Life Cycle Costs. HOMER also simulates the operation of the system by providing the calculation of the Energy Balance for every 8,760 hours in a year. If a sensitivity analysis is required, HOMER will repeat the simulation process for each variable sensitivity [CITATION_1] . Relative error of about 3% yearly and monthly Relative error of about 10% [22] [23]. Figure 5 shows is architecture HOMER with three main parts: input, simulation and output.",
